reviews.review_text: Terrible sound This show sounds terrible.  Overdriven/distorted bass is high in the mix and everything else is low and inaudible.
Was this show played in a fishbowl the sound is basically awful.

Released as Dick's Picks 30 Not sure why this show is still on the archives since it is released as Dick's Picks 30. Obviously, officially released material sounds a hellu 'lot better than what you get here. It sounds like you're right on stage with Dick's Picks. You hear a lot more on-stage banter which adds to the great recording of this show. The Music (especially Jerry's pedal steel on Looks Like Rain) sounds great . The band used these gigs to help pay for the now infamous Europe '72 tour. Excellent show imho. Go get buy it !! and help support the band ! Rating is for Dick's Picks version of this show.
IT was 1972 this was as good as it got. Well it was 1972 recording wasn't perfected yet. Bootleg albums and reel to reel was all we could get. I for one was grateful at the time.
